…adjourns plenary till January 18, 2022 The Senate today passed an aggregate expenditure of N17.12 trillion naira budget as against the N16.39 trillion sum presented by President Muhammadu Buhari for the 2022 fiscal year.  The passage followed the consideration of a report by the Appropriations Committee on the 2022 Appropriations Bill, presented by Chairman of the Committee, Senator Barau Jibrin, explained that the budget is predicated upon 1.88million barrels per day Daily crude Oil Production, US$62 as against $US57 proposed by the executive arm of government, exchange rate pegged at N410.15/US$1, Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Rate at 4.2 and Inflation Rate at 13 percent.  The lawmaker noted that out of the total sum passed, N869.7billion is for Statutory Transfer; N6.9trillion is for Recurrent Expenditure; N5.5trillion is for Capital Expenditure; and N3.8trillion is for Debt Service.  In his concluding remarks, President of the Senate, Senator Ahmad Lawan lauded the lawmakers who worked so hard to ensure that the 2022 budget was passed in time to keep with the new tradition of operating an annual national budget from January to December. The Senate, after passing the 2022 budget, adjourned plenary till January 18, 2022 for the Christmas break.